This paper focuses on integrating knowledge graphs into pre-trained language models for natural language processing tasks, which is a common topic in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a novel transformer-based model for knowledge representation learning, which involves machine learning techniques such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of knowledge graphs for information retrieval (cs.IR) and data management (cs.DB).
